Institute of Technology]] and graduated in 1995 with a Bachelor's degree in Engineering. In 2006, he received his Master's degree in Business Administration from [[New York University Stern School of Business|Stern School of Business, New York]]. \u00a0In 2015, he also earned a certificate in [[Design thinking|Design Thinking]] from [[Stanford University]]. He is certified in board governance and is a [[National Association of Corporate Directors]] (NACD) Governance Fellow since 2013.\n\n== Career ==\nHe started his career as a [[software engineer]] working on the then-emerging [[Rich web application|Internet applications]] and then moved on to work as a [[digital strategy]] and transformation consultant for [[Rodale, Inc.|Rodale Inc]]. The publisher of healthy active living magazines including [[Men's Health|Men\u2019s Health]], [[Backpacker (magazine)|Backpacker]], [[Runner's World|Runner\u2019s World]], Prevention; and books including Al Gore\u2019s Inconvenient Truth and South Beach Diet.\n\nIn 2006, Karthik joined [[RELX]] (formerly [[Reed Elsevier]]) as [[Vice president|Vice President]] Interactive Media and Sales Management for 44 brands including [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]], [[Broadcasting & Cable]], [[Multichannel News]], Interior Design and Hotels . He then went on to lead the Global Pharma Business and [[e-commerce]] channel at [[Elsevier, Inc.|Elsevier Inc]] as Senior [[Vice president|Vice President]] & [[General manager|General Manager]]. He then took on the Global Clinical Reference & Workflow business at [[Elsevier|Elsevier Inc]] and launched products that won industry recognition including Best in KLAS and [[Frost & Sullivan]] Technology Innovation awards.\n\nHe joined [[Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica|Britannica]] in November 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.connectedtoindia.com/indian-american-karthik-krishnan-appointed-ceo-of-encyclopedia-britannica-group-3362.html|title=Indian-American Karthik Krishnan appointed CEO of Encyclopedia Britannica Group|website=www.connectedtoindia.com|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cio.com/article/3525005/encyclopedia-britannica-ceo-karthik-krishnan-explains-how-he-works-with-his-cto-and-cpo.html|title=Encyclopedia Britannica CEO explains how he works with his CTO and CPO|last=Trueman|first=Charlotte|date=2019-04-29|website=CIO|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiawest.com/news/global_indian/indian-american-karthik-krishnan-named-global-ceo-of-encyclopaedia-britannica-group/article_8af7a4e4-e782-11e7-a1b2-131f9b162cf7.html|title=Indian American Karthik Krishnan Named Global CEO of Encyclopaedia Britannica Group|last=Reporter|first=India-West Staff|website=India West|language=en|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> He launched a pair of ideas having these two themes as moto:\n\n1. Elevate better information in the digital universe\n\n2. Transform learning inside and outside the classroom<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.asiaoutlookmag.com/industry-insights/article/725-exclusive-interview-encyclopdia-britannica-ceo-karthik-krishnan|title=Asia Outlook Magazine|website=www.asiaoutlookmag.com|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nKarthik Krishnan firstly introduced Britannica Insights, a [[Google Chrome]] browser extension<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://securityboulevard.com/2020/02/concentric-applies-deep-learning-algorithms-to-data-security/|title=Concentric Applies Deep Learning Algorithms to Data Security|last=February 3|first=Michael Vizard on|last2=2020|date=2020-02-03|website=Security Boulevard|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> that allows users who are searching to cut through the clutter, buy time, study more and ensure that the results are almost as same as the results that show up on search engines like [[Google]], [[Yahoo!|Yahoo]], and [[Bing (search engine)|Bing]]. Then came the next product observed by the concept of Britannica School Insights,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wgnradio.com/the-download/